  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance resilience of the most vulnerable community to cope with waterlogging in Satkhira and Jessor</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to improve community
capacity to reduce waterlogging risks and to adopt resilient livelihoods strategies for improved food and
nutrition security. It includes small scale risk mitigation measures to reduce physical risks as well as
protection of the livelihoods. The project also aims to support affected households to strengthen
productivity, improve access to social services in order to achieve resilience against waterlogging. The
project will promote land and water based adaptive farming practices for achieving resilient
livelihoods.
The project will target total 2500 landless daily labourers, marginal and small farming households.
Area: Satkhira District, Satkhira Sadar, Tala and
Kolaroa Upazila, Dhulihar, Fingri, Kumira,
Khalilnagar, Jogikhali and Joynagar union;
Jessore District, Keshobpur Upazila,
Biddyanandakathi and Trimohini union.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under the DesHARI consortium, the proposed project aims to improve community capacity to reduce waterlogging risks and to adopt resilient livelihoods strategies for improved food and nutrition security. It includes small scale risk mitigation measures to reduce physical risks as well as protection of the livelihoods. The project also aims to support affected households to strengthen productivity, improve access to social services in order to achieve resilience against waterlogging. The project will promote land and water based adaptive farming practices for achieving resilient livelihoods.</narrative>
  </description>
